openapi: 3.0.0 info: description: Real-time bus prediction methods. title: Real-Time Bus Predictions version: "1.0" x-apisguru-categories: - transport x-logo: url: https://twitter.com/wmata/profile_image?size=original x-origin: - format: swagger url: https://developer.wmata.com/docs/services/5476365e031f590f38092508/export?DocumentFormat=Swagger version: "2.0" x-providerName: wmata.com x-serviceName: bus-realtime security: - apiKeyHeader: [] - apiKeyQuery: [] tags: [] paths: /Predictions: get: description: "

Description

\r \r

Returns next bus arrival times at a stop.

\r \r

Response Elements

\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r
ElementDescription
Predictions\r Array containing bus predictions (NextBusPrediction).\r
StopNameFull name of the given StopID.
\r
\r NextBusPrediction Elements\r
\r
DirectionNumDenotes a binary direction (0 or 1) of the bus. There is no\r specific mapping to direction, but a different value for the same\r route signifies that the buses are traveling in opposite\r directions. Use the DirectionText element to show the actual\r destination of the bus.
DirectionTextCustomer-friendly description of direction and destination for\r a bus.
MinutesMinutes until bus arrival at this stop. Numeric value.
RouteIDBase route name as shown on the bus. This can be used in other\r bus-related methods. Note that all variants will be shown as their\r base route names (i.e.: 10Av1 and 10Av2 will be shown as 10A).
TripIDTrip identifier. This can be correlated with the data in our\r bus schedule information as well as bus positions.
VehicleIDBus identifier. This can be correlated with results returned\r from bus positions.
" operationId: 5476365e031f5909e4fe331e parameters: - description: 7-digit regional stop ID. in: query name: StopID required: true schema: type: string enum: - "1001195" default: "1001195" responses: "200": description: Default response code. content: text/xml: examples: response: value: >- 0 North to Bwi - Thurgood Marshall Airport 8 B30 6794838 6217 1 South to Greenbelt Station 37 B30 6794868 6217 0 North to Bwi - Thurgood Marshall Airport 48 B30 6794839 6213 1 South to Greenbelt Station 77 B30 6794869 6213 Bwi Airport + Stop 2 "400": description: Response from invalid Stop ID. content: application/xml: examples: response: value: Stop Id not specified, invalid, or does not exist. summary: XML - Next Buses /json/jPredictions: get: description: "
